{"candidates": [{"claim": "The present failure is a manifest-policy gap: the immutable manifest freezes role routes and scratch/bridge policies but does not bind school conditioning to distinct configured routes. The scheduler iterates schools as prompt provenance but not as distinct wire-contract routes, creating an ambiguity where the harness attempts to express school-specific orchestration through model conditioning rather than deterministic route assignment. The harness should own school-to-route binding in the manifest; model calls should remain bounded content functions unaware of school routing. This preserves open-ended reasoning (C10) by ensuring the model receives only a single bounded responsibility (C4) while the harness deterministically selects which route, budget, and scratch/bridge policy applies.", "mechanism": "Deterministic components: manifest freeze binds school identifiers to route leases (extending run_manifest.py:412-500); scheduler resolves school to route lease before dispatch (extending scheduler.py:410-520); adapter verifies route lease against manifest binding (extending adapter.py:300-430); budget reservations enforced per-route against shared ceiling (budget.py:79-158). Model-call components: adapter performs schema-bound call with strict wire contract; model receives school as prompt/provenance conditioning only. Typed interfaces: SchoolRouteBinding{school_id, route_id, budget_tier, scratch_policy, bridge_policy} -> RouteLease -> WireContract. Transition semantics: manifest freeze is atomic; school-to-route binding is conflict-safe (run_manifest.py:1328-1406); route lease issuance is append-only event. Manifest/events/replay implications: replay materializes formal state only (harness.py:69-116); school route bindings are part of immutable manifest and replay deterministically. Evidence and security behaviour: adapter rejects mechanism drift (adapter.py:300-430); budget enforced before dispatch. Migration: extend manifest schema to include school-to-route binding map; scheduler reads binding before dispatch; no change to model adapter contract. Retained open-ended freedom: model still produces conjectures, criticisms, scratch content within its bounded responsibility. Strongest likely failure mode: binding all schools to the same route silently, making the binding a no-op. Falsifying tests: replay a run with two schools and assert each dispatched call's route lease matches the manifest binding; assert scheduler raises if no binding exists for a conditioned school; assert manifest digest changes when school-to-route binding changes.", "counterconditions": ["If schools are documented as prompt-provenance-only conditioning with no route implication, the binding is unnecessary", "If the adapter already implicitly selects routes based on school context, the gap may not exist", "If future chat services require dynamic school assignment post-manifest-freeze, static binding would be too rigid"], "typicality": 0.92, "analogy": {"source_memory_refs": ["731938a568fa4a6200024c0bcf743cf46f14b0ead5088c5e33ef1ac2c558d5b1", "f1f1461eefbbba50ea2f9d6f87e9aed22230fa4538fe1c22fddbc15aaeec0b83"], "shared_structure": ["Immutable policy freeze binds runtime dispatch decisions", "Append-only events record consequential transitions", "Replay materializes canonical state from events"], "disanalogies": ["Route binding is pre-execution policy, not runtime evidence", "School-to-route binding is a configuration concern, not a reasoning artifact"], "transfer_claims": ["Just as the manifest freezes scratch/bridge policies, it should freeze school-to-route bindings to prevent prompt-delegated route selection"], "overturn_conditions": ["If schools are purely prompt conditioning with no route semantics, the analogy to policy freeze does not apply"]}, "optional_refs": ["5cd28b5078a81b9472fc2110237d7e3d06791b980f0bde986add9ae797e643e3", "b5f7cb1f66a4325cbb69a9eaf559d87401852b207dd3fbb7bcb88b67ce358950", "bf597433295f50d98c674f9244